#string STR_PER_CORE_HT_DISABLE                                 #language en-US "Per-core HT Disable"
#string STR_PER_CORE_HT_DISABLE_HELP                            #language en-US "Defines the per-core HT disable mask where: 1 - Disable selected logical core HT, 0 - is ignored. Input is in HEX and each bit maps to a logical core. Ex. A value of '1F' would disable HT for cores 4,3,2,1 and 0. Default is 0, all cores have HT enabled. Range is 0 - 0x7F for max 8 cores. You can only disable up to MAX_CORE_COUNT - 1."

